task_description: Facing the building to your South-East (approx. 138°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: I need to see the full height of the building to estimate it, so I will start by looking up to find the roof.
My heading was reset and I'm no longer facing the building; I need to turn back to the target building at approximately 138° and look up further to see the roof.
I still can't see the top of the building, so I need to look up further to see the roofline.
My heading was reset again; I need to turn back to the building at 138° and look up even higher, aiming for a 60° pitch to see the roof.
I can now see the roofline and the ground; the building appears to be about 7 stories high, and assuming each story is approximately 3.5 meters, the total height is around 24.5 meters.
